Are two elements equivalent?

Source: R/equal.R
html_equal.Rd

Checks if two selenider_element objects point to the same element on the page. html_equal() is equivalent to using ==, but allows you to specify a timeout value if needed.

Usage

html_equal(x, y, timeout = NULL)

# S3 method for selenider_element
==(e1, e2)

Arguments

x, y, e1, e2

selenider_element objects to compare.

timeout

How long to wait for the elements to be present.

Value

TRUE or FALSE.

Examples

<div></div>
<div class='second'>
  <p></p>
</div>
"
